  "bio": [
    "Carlos March Delgado was president of $2.5 billion (net assets) Banca March, Spain's only 100% family-owned bank, for four decades until 2015.",
    "Carlos and his billionaire brother Juan March Delgado are grandchildren of Banca March's founder, Juan March (d. 1962), who started the business in Palma de Mallorca in 1926.",
    "After stepping down as a director of Banca March in 2024, Carlos remains chairman of $5 billion (net assets) investment company Corporación Financiera Alba, which is also nearly 100% family-owned.",
    "Carlos and Juan March Delgado own 69% of Banca March and 42% of Corporación Financiera Alba combined (excluding Banca March's 15% stake in Corporación Financiera Alba)."
  ],
